fields.description: Ji-hye Lee is the CEO of OYORI ASIA, a South Korean social enterprise operating many restaurants in Asia with a business model that aims to support women in poverty and youths in communities where the restaurants operate. She is also an Adjunct Professor at Ewha Women’s University where she teaches ‘social enterprise incubating’ and ‘young social entrepreneurs mentoring’ topics.

Ken Ito works for AVPN as Japan Advisor. He has a bachelor degree in economics and MBA in International Management from The American Graduate School of International Management (Thunderbird) in the United States. Ken spent ten years in the private sector, with his last position at GE Capital. He subsequently joined the Institute for Strategic Leadership (ISL) to launch the Center for Social Innovation, to promote social innovation through its leadership training programs.
fields.summary: Ken Ito is a Japan Advisor for Asian Venture Philanthropy Network (AVPN).

fields.description: Sinee joined Ashoka in 1997 to launch Asia's first Citizen Base Initiative, nurturing the citizen sector to formulate an agenda independent from government and international donors. As Country Representative since 1998, she has facilitated the fifth oldest Ashoka Fellowship, the Venture program, and the Southeast Asia network of partners. Sinee has been active in Thailand's civic movement since the historic protests for democratic reforms in 1970s. She has extensive experience in cross-cultural work under difficult circumstances – with refugees, hilltribe minorities, slum residents, women and children. Sinee matches in-depth understanding of grassroots movements with her wide-ranging connections in Thailand and Southeast Asia.

Patcharaporn Pansuwan is Co-Founder of Opendream, technology-focused social enterprise based in Bangkok and Chiang Mai, Thailand. 

She focuses on bringing Team Opendream to be aware of social impact and its sustainability as well as creation of the most usable and impactful projects for digital health care, life education and livelihood development.
I converted design to markup(HTML, CSS) and made them compatible in every browsers.

Sunit Shrestha is founder & Managing Director of ChangeFusion, a non-profit institute under Thai Rural Reconstruction Movement Foundation under the Royal Patronage.  

ChangeFusion supports social enterprises in various areas including mobile-based disease surveillance, appropriate technology for sustainable agriculture for lower income rural farmers, sustainable tourism and more. 

He also collaborate to design the setup of social investment funds for emerging social entrepreneurs in Thailand & Asia through UnLtd Programs in Southeast Asia, Change Ventures and B-KIND Fund, Thailand's first Socially Responsible Investment Fund.

He also engaged in different areas of social innovation researches such the development of ecosystems for sustainable agriculture in Asia with Oxfam  as well as the feasibility study of Asian Social Stock Exchange with the ADB.
